title: Grateful Dead Live at Alpine Valley Music Theatre on 1987-06-28
lineage: The Master Cassettes were played back with Azimuth  adjustment and Dolby B decoding on a Nakamichi CD1 into a  Korg MR1000 at DSF 1 bit 5.6MHz. Subsequent conversion to  24/96 AIFF done via Korg Audiogate software. Redbook CDR  standard 16/44.1 files were created using Bias Peak, Izotope Ozone's  MBIT+ (for all dithering), and Weiss Saracon SRC (all sample rate conversions).
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Little Red Rooster, Bird Song, Jack Straw

Set 2

Mississippi Half Step, Women Are Smarter, Ship of Fools, Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Space-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Not Fade Away-> The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text: Best of the sources I think this source sounds better than the others. Much cleaner and at the correct speed. Thank you!

My first show, my first dose I was enthralled by the show with devils in the sky riding the clouds. I also thoroughly enjoyed the pre-show Bob Marley music and the post-show Sinatra. I remember Alpine's sewage system shut down and there were a hundred of us chanting "we want to shit!" outside the locked bathrooms.
